comments.body:
Ok, I misunderstood what you said above about the versions prior to 3.5.0-alpha. Looking at your log lines, the client isn't really completing the connection establishment. "CONNECTING" here means that it is still trying  to connect:

{noformat}
[zk: localhost:2181(CONNECTING) 0] create /dog moon
{noformat}

and you should be seeing something like this instead:

{noformat}
[zk: localhost:2181(CONNECTED) 0]
{noformat}

Is there an issue with docker when trying to connect to localhost:2181?
